  116. ‌  let read_stdout =
  117.     let size = 50 in
  118.     let b = Bytes.create size in
  119.     let buffer = Buffer.create 100 in
  120.     let rec read_toplevel_stdout () =
  121.       match Unix.select[stdout_out][][] 0. with
  122.       | [_a], _, _ ->
  123.           let n = Unix.read stdout_out b 0 size in
  124.           Buffer.add_subbytes buffer b 0 n;

  126.       | _  -> ()
  127.     in
  128.     fun () ->

  162. ‌  let report_printer =
  163.     (* Extend [printer_register_locs] *)
  164.     let pp self ppf report =

  192. ‌  let exec (_,ppf) p =
  193.     try
  194.       ignore @@ Toploop.execute_phrase true ppf p
  195.     with exn ->
  196.       let bt = Printexc.get_raw_backtrace () in
  197.       begin try Location.report_exception (snd error_fmt) exn
  198.       with _ ->
  199.         eprintf "Uncaught exception: %s\n%s\n"
  200.           (Printexc.to_string exn)
  201.           (Printexc.raw_backtrace_to_string bt)
  202.       end

  204.   let parse fname mode s =
  205.     let lex = Lexing.from_string s in
  206.     Location.init lex fname;
  207.     Location.input_name := fname;
  208.     Location.input_lexbuf := Some lex;
  209.     try
  210.       match mode with
  211.       | Toplevel -> Parse.toplevel_phrase lex
  212.       | Verbatim -> Parsetree.Ptop_def (Parse.implementation lex)
  213.       | Signature ->
  214.           let sign = Parse.interface lex in
  215.           let name = Location.mknoloc "wrap" in
  216.           let str =
  217.             Ast_helper.[Str.modtype @@ Mtd.mk ~typ:(Mty.signature sign) name] in
  218.           Parsetree.Ptop_def str
  219.     with
  220.     | Lexer.Error _ | Syntaxerr.Error _ ->
  221.         raise (Phrase_parsing s)

  223. ‌  let take x = let r = !x in x := []; r

  225. ‌  let read_output ()  =
  226.     let warnings = take warnings in
  227.     let error = flush_fmt error_fmt in
  228.     let values =
  229.       replace_first ~!{|^#\( *\*\)* *|} "" @@ flush_fmt out_fmt in
  230.     (* the inner ( *\* )* group is here to clean the starting "*"
  231.        introduced for multiline comments *)
  232.     let underlined = take locs in
  233.     let stdout = read_stdout () in
  234.     { values; warnings; error; stdout; underlined }

  236.   (** exec and ignore all output from the toplevel *)
  237. ‌  let eval b =
  238.     let s = Buffer.contents b in
  239.     let ast = Parse.toplevel_phrase (Lexing.from_string s) in
  240.     exec out_fmt ast;
  241.     ignore (read_output());
  242.     Buffer.reset b

  244. end

  254.     "ocamltex: ";
  255.   Toplevel.init ()

  263.   (** Interpreter output status *)
  264. ‌  type status =
  265.     | Ok
  266.     | Warning of int
  267.     | Error

  269. ‌  type kind =
  270.     | Annotation (** Local annotation: [ [@@expect (*annotation*) ] ]*)
  271.     | Option (** Global environment option:
  272.                  [\begin{caml_example}[option[=value]]
  273.                  ...
  274.                  \end{caml_example}] *)

  276.   (** Pretty printer for status *)
  277. ‌  let pp_status ppf = function
  278.     | Error -> Format.fprintf ppf "error"
  279.     | Ok -> Format.fprintf ppf "ok"
  280.     | Warning n -> Format.fprintf ppf "warning %d" n

  282.   (** Pretty printer for status preceded with an undefined determinant *)
  283. ‌  let pp_a_status ppf = function
  284.     | Error -> Format.fprintf ppf "an error"
  285.     | Ok -> Format.fprintf ppf "an ok"
  286.     | Warning n -> Format.fprintf ppf "a warning %d" n

  288.   (** {1 Related latex environment } *)
  289. ‌  let env = function
  290.     | Error -> error
  291.     | Warning _ -> warning
  292.     | Ok -> ok_output

  294.   (** {1 Exceptions } *)
  295.   exception Parsing_error of kind * string

  297. ‌  type source =
  298.     {
  299.       file : string;
  300.       lines : int * int;
  301.       phrase : string;
  302.       output : string
  303.     }
  304. ‌  type unexpected_report = {source : source; expected : status; got : status}
  305.   exception Unexpected_status of unexpected_report

  307. ‌  let print_source ppf {file; lines = (start, stop); phrase; output} =
  308.     Format.fprintf ppf "%s, lines %d to %d:\n\"\n%s\n\"\n\"\n%s\n\"."
  309.       file start stop phrase output

  311. ‌  let print_unexpected {source; expected; got} =
  312.     if expected = Ok then
  313.       Toplevel.eprintf
  314.         "Error when evaluating a caml_example environment in %a\n\
  315.          Unexpected %a status.\n\
  316.          If %a status was expected, add an [@@expect %a] annotation.\n"
  317.         print_source source
  318.         pp_status got
  319.         pp_a_status got
  320.         pp_status got
  321.     else
  322.       Toplevel.eprintf
  323.         "Error when evaluating a guarded caml_example environment in %a\n\
  324.          Unexpected %a status, %a status was expected.\n\
  325.          If %a status was in fact expected, change the status annotation to \
  326.          [@@expect %a].\n"
  327.         print_source source
  328.         pp_status got
  329.         pp_a_status expected
  330.         pp_a_status got
  331.         pp_status got;
  332.     flush stderr

  334. ‌  let print_parsing_error k s =
  335.     match k with
  336.     | Option ->
  337.         Toplevel.eprintf
  338.           "Unknown caml_example option: [%s].\n\
  339.            Supported options are \"ok\",\"error\", or \"warning=n\" (with n \
  340.            a warning number).\n" s
  341.     | Annotation ->
  342.         Toplevel.eprintf
  343.           "Unknown caml_example phrase annotation: [@@expect %s].\n\
  344.            Supported annotations are [@@expect ok], [@@expect error],\n\
  345.            and [@@expect warning n] (with n a warning number).\n" s

  347.   (** {1 Output analysis} *)
  348. ‌  let catch_error = function
  349.     | "" -> None
  350.     | _ -> Some Error

  352. ‌  let catch_warning =
  353.     function
  354.     | [] -> None
  355.     | s :: _ when string_match ~!{|
  356. *Warning \([0-9]+\)\( \[[a-z-]+\]\)?:|} s 0 ->
  357.         Some (Warning (int_of_string @@ matched_group 1 s))
  358.     | _ -> None

  360. ‌  let status ws es =
  361.     match catch_warning ws, catch_error es with
  362.     | Some w, _ -> w
  363.     | None, Some e -> e
  364.     | None, None -> Ok

  366.   (** {1 Parsing caml_example options } *)

  368.   (** Parse [warning=n] options for caml_example options *)
  369. ‌  let parse_warning s =
  370.     if string_match ~!{|warning=\([0-9]+\)|} s 0 then
  371.       Some (Warning (int_of_string @@ matched_group 1 s))
  372.     else
  373.       None

  375.   (** Parse [warning n] annotations *)
  376. ‌  let parse_local_warning s =
  377.     if string_match ~!{|warning \([0-9]+\)|} s 0 then
  378.       Some (Warning (int_of_string @@ matched_group 1 s))
  379.     else
  380.       None

  382. ‌  let parse_error s =
  383.     if s="error" then Some Error else None

  385. ‌  let parse_ok s =
  386.     if s = "ok" then Some Ok else None

  388.   (** Parse the environment-wide expected status output *)
  389. ‌  let expected s =
  390.     match parse_warning s, parse_error s with
  391.     | Some w, _ -> w
  392.     | None, Some e -> e
  393.     | None, None -> raise (Parsing_error (Option,s))

  395.   (** Parse the local (i.e. phrase-wide) expected status output *)
  396. ‌  let local_expected s =
  397.     match parse_local_warning s, parse_error s, parse_ok s with
  398.     | Some w, _, _ -> w
  399.     | None, Some e, _ -> e
  400.     | None, None, Some ok -> ok
  401.     | None, None, None -> raise (Parsing_error (Annotation,s))

  403. end

  405. module Text_transform = struct

  407. ‌  type kind =
  408.     | Underline
  409.     | Ellipsis

  411. ‌  type t = { kind : kind; start : int; stop : int}
  412.   exception Intersection of
  413.       {
  414.         line : int;
  415.         file : string;
  416.         left : t;
  417.         right : t;
  418.       }

  420. ‌  let pp ppf = function
  421.     | Underline -> Format.fprintf ppf "underline"
  422.     | Ellipsis -> Format.fprintf ppf "ellipsis"

  424. ‌  let underline start stop = { kind = Underline; start; stop}
  425. ‌  let escape_specials s =
  426.     s
  427.     |> global_replace ~!{|\$|} {|$\textdollar$|}

  429. ‌  let rec apply_transform input (pos,underline_stop,out) t =
  430.     if pos >= String.length input then pos, underline_stop, out
  431.     else match underline_stop with
  432.       | Some stop when stop <= t.start ->
  433.           let f = escape_specials (String.sub input ~pos ~len:(stop - pos)) in
  434.           let out =  camleunderline :: f :: out in
  435.           apply_transform input (stop,None,out) t
  436.       | _ ->
  437.           let out =
  438.             escape_specials (String.sub input ~pos ~len:(t.start - pos))::out in
  439.           match t.kind with
  440.           | Ellipsis -> t.stop, underline_stop, latex_escape {|\ldots|} :: out
  441.           | Underline ->
  442.               t.start, Some t.stop, camlbunderline :: out

  444.   (** Merge consecutive transforms:
  445.        - drop nested underline transform
  446.        - raise an error with transforms nested under an ellipsis
  447.        - raise an error when consecutive transforms partially overlap
  448.   *)
  449. ‌  let merge_transforms file line ts =
  450.     let rec merge (active, active_stack, acc) t =
  451.       if active.stop <= t.start then
  452.          (* no overlap, the next transform starts after the end of the current
  453.             active transform *)
  454.         match active_stack with
  455.         | [] ->
  456.             (* there were no other active transforms, the new transform becomes
  457.                the active one *)
  458.             t, [], t :: acc
  459.         | last :: active_stack ->
  460.             (* we check that [t] is still conflict-free with our parent
  461.                transforms *)
  462.             merge (last, active_stack,acc) t
  463.       else if active.stop < t.stop (* not nested *) then
  464.         raise (Intersection {line; file; left = active; right=t})
  465.       else (* nested transforms *)
  466.         match active.kind, t.kind  with
  467.         | Ellipsis, _ -> (* no nesting allowed under an ellipsis *)
  468.             raise (Intersection {line; file; left = active; right=t})
  469.         | Underline, Ellipsis -> (* underlined ellipsis are allowed *)
  470.             (t , active :: active_stack, t :: acc)
  471.         | Underline, Underline ->
  472.             (* multiple underlining are flattened to one *)
  473.             (t, active :: active_stack, acc)
  474.     in
  475.     match ts with
  476.     | [] -> []
  477.     | a :: q ->
  478.         let _, _, ts = List.fold_left ~f:merge ~init:(a,[],[a]) q in
  479.         List.rev ts

  481. ‌  let apply ts file line s =
  482.     (* remove duplicated transforms that can appear due to
  483.         duplicated parse tree elements. For instance,
  484.         [let f : (_ [@ellipsis] = ()] is transformed to
  485.         [let f: (_ [@ellipsis]) = (():(_ [@ellipsis])] with the same location
  486.         for the two ellipses. *)
  487.     let ts = List.sort_uniq compare ts in
  488.     let ts = List.sort (fun x y -> compare x.start y.start) ts in
  489.     let ts = merge_transforms file line ts in
  490.     let last, underline, ls =
  491.       List.fold_left ~f:(apply_transform s) ~init:(0,None,[]) ts in
  492.     let last, ls = match underline with
  493.       | None -> last, ls
  494.       | Some stop ->
  495.           let f = escape_specials (String.sub s ~pos:last ~len:(stop - last)) in
  496.           stop, camleunderline :: f :: ls in
  497.     let ls =
  498.       let n = String.length s in
  499.       if last = n then ls else
  500.         escape_specials (String.sub s last (n-last)) :: ls in
  501.     String.concat "" (List.rev ls)
  502. end

  552.             {Text_transform.kind=Ellipsis; start; stop }
  553.             :: !transforms

  555.           check_nested ();

  572.          raise (Unmatched_ellipsis {kind="left"; start; stop })
